## Early game

**Naeglar** on Eris (Hive) is the only documented Mutagen Sample source on
the planet: the wiki's drop tables show a Rotation B Hive Sabotage resource
cache with roughly a 15.5% chance for 3 samples. Mutagen Sample has no enemy
drop table, so this cache is effectively the entire farm — clear the Hive
efficiently, bank the Rotation B reward, and reset.

## Mid & late game

Since Eris doesn't have a second Mutagen Sample node, the endgame upgrade is
running **Naeglar** (Hive, Steel Path) with a full 4-player squad instead of
solo. Each player's own mission completion rolls the resource cache table
independently, so a full squad effectively multiplies the number of caches
found per run. Because Mutagen Sample comes from an end-of-mission resource
cache rather than an enemy drop, Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path
passive don't apply here — squad size, not drop-chance buffs, is what scales
the farm. (Deimos' Formido has a similar cache for players who've reached the
Cambion Drift, but Eris is the self-contained option for this planet's
farming path.)

